Parse lipid name with a specific grammar.

parseLipidNameWithGrammar.Rd

parseLipidName reads the provided lipid name based on grammar and returns structural information as a named vector. Will return a vector with the "Grammar" element set to "NOT_PARSEABLE" if none of the parsers was able to parse the provided name with the provided grammar successfully. If any error was raised, returns an empty vector.

parseLipidNameWithGrammar(lipidName, grammar)

Arguments

lipidName

The lipid name to parse.
grammar

The grammar to use. One of "Goslin", "GoslinFragments", "SwissLipids", "LipidMaps", "HMDB"

Value

Named vector with details of the lipid, empty vector otherwise.

Examples

parseLipidNameWithGrammar("PC 32:1", "Goslin")
#>                 Normalized Name                   Original Name 
#>                       "PC 32:1"                       "PC 32:1" 
#>                         Grammar             Lipid Maps Category
